    <sect1>
        <title>Installation on Windows</title>
        <para>Use the Windows installer to install. During installation the <guimenuitem>Start Menu
                Folder</guimenuitem> is created and a shortcuts are added to the folder which
            enabled starting and to uninstalling of the program.</para>
        <procedure>
            <title>To install on Windows:</title>
            <step>
                <para><link
                        xlink:href="https://subsurface-divelog.org/download/subsurface-&productversion;.exe"
                        >Download the installer</link>.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Execute the installer.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Click <guibutton>Yes</guibutton> to allow the installation.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Accept the software license.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Choose the install path (default should be reasonable in most cases).</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title>Installation on MacOS</title>
        <procedure>
            <title>To install on MacOS:</title>
            <step>
                <para><link
                        xlink:href="https://subsurface-divelog.org/download/Subsurface-&productversion;.dmg"
                        >Download the installer</link>.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Execute the installer.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Locate the <application>Subsurface.app</application> file in the
                        <guilabel>Finder Sidebar</guilabel>.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Drag the application into the <filename class="directory"
                        >/Applications</filename> folder to install.</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title>Installation on Linux</title>
        <para>The project makes dedicated binaries available for a number of Linux flavours as well
            as a generic <application>AppImage</application> that should work on most any Linux
            distributions.</para>
        <sect2>
            <title>Installation on DEB-based Systems</title>
            <para>The project maintains a Personal Package Archive (<acronym>PPA</acronym>)
                repository.</para>
            <para><command>ppa:subsurface/subsurface</command></para>
            <procedure>
                <title>To install on DEB-based systems:</title>
                <step>
                    <para>Add the repository.</para>
                    <para><command>sudo apt-add-repository
                        ppa:subsurface/subsurface</command></para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Update the software list.</para>
                    <para><command>sudo apt-get update</command></para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Install the program.</para>
                    <para><command>sudo apt-get install subsurface</command></para>
                </step>
            </procedure>
            <important>
                <para>Make sure you are getting a current version with all its Qt5
                    dependencies.</para>
            </important>
            <procedure>
                <title>To install on older DEB-based systems:</title>
                <para>Installation on older DEB-based systems is possible but required changing the
                    release name of the distribution.</para>
                <step>
                    <para>Add the repository.</para>
                    <para><command>sudo apt-add-repository
                        ppa:subsurface/subsurface</command></para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Update the software list.</para>
                    <para><command>sudo apt-get update</command></para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Install the program.</para>
                    <para><command>sudo apt-get install subsurface</command></para>
                </step>
            </procedure>
        </sect2>
        <sect2>
            <title>Installation on RPM-based Systems</title>
            <para>The project maintains a build service project page from which it is possible to download and
                install.</para>
            <procedure>
                <title>To install on RPM-based systems:</title>
                <step>
                    <para>Click Here to display the build service project page.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Click <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> to by-pass the <guilabel>Search
                            settings</guilabel> dialog.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Select your Operating System.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Choose your installation method:</para>
                    <simplelist>
                        <member>Add a repository and install manually.</member>
                        <member>Grab binary packages directly.</member>
                    </simplelist>
                </step>
            </procedure>
        </sect2>
